1
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:11,233
♪I've braved the storms, walked through the rain♪

2
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:14,633
♪Seen the highs and lows along the way♪

3
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:18,033
♪But you stay quiet, never change♪

4
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:21,633
♪Like a child who dreams beneath the stars♪

5
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:25,033
♪I've read the story in your eyes♪

6
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:28,533
♪And finally, nothing's left to hide♪

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:32,133
♪You won't give in to a world so cold♪

8
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:35,733
♪So you wander through it on your own♪

9
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:39,333
♪Maybe fate has drawn us near♪

10
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:42,333
♪Just to help you learn to believe♪

11
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:45,500
♪Everything you've questioned deep inside♪

12
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:49,733
♪I'll be the proof you need♪

13
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,167
♪I've made my choice♪

14
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:54,133
♪For you, I'll be brave and break the rules♪

15
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,367
♪What's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?♪

16
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,933
♪One day, all of this will turn into memories♪

17
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:04,367
♪Every storm we faced will turn into our life's scenery♪

18
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:08,033
♪For you, I'll be brave and break the rules♪

19
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:11,267
♪What's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?♪

20
00:01:11,967 --> 00:01:14,833
♪Even if, in the end, the whole world turns against me♪

21
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:18,267
♪I won't regret having loved you♪

22
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:21,933
♪With all my heart♪

23
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:25,767
♪I've held you close♪

24
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:29,467
♪Walked by your side♪

25
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:33,933
♪And loved the fire that burned inside you♪

26
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,467
[The First Frost]

27
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:36,967
[Adapted from the novel of the same name by Zhu Yi on www.jjwxc.net]

28
00:01:37,233 --> 00:01:40,167
[Beiyu High School]

29
00:01:40,167 --> 00:01:42,267
Do you know how expensive dance lessons are?

30
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,133
You're not a kid anymore.

31
00:01:44,867 --> 00:01:46,867
It's time to give up those unrealistic fantasies.

32
00:01:46,867 --> 00:01:48,100
I don't need you to spend money hiring a teacher.

33
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:49,233
Can I just practice on my own?

34
00:01:49,367 --> 00:01:50,433
Where will you be practicing?

35
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:52,633
In your aunt's living room?

36
00:01:53,233 --> 00:01:54,633
Or are you renting a dance studio?

37
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:56,967
It's expensive, even by the hour.

38
00:02:22,067 --> 00:02:23,000
Your Uncle Zheng's new clinic

39
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,567
has been losing money

40
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,533
and we're also struggling financially.

41
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,600
Doesn't Zheng Kejia need money

42
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,700
to study art as well?

43
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:33,667
If she didn't study art

44
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:35,367
she couldn't even make it to college.

45
00:02:35,367 --> 00:02:37,167
Does that mean I have to give up dancing?

46
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:47,833
I got it.

47
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:52,733
Why are we looking at the elementary school?

48
00:05:54,267 --> 00:05:54,933
Come with me.

49
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:02,933
Where are we going?

50
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:05,000
Did we come here

51
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,833
to climb stairs today?

52
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,400
Are you tired, my junior?

53
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:35,500
What are we doing here?

54
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,400
Since you can't dance anywhere else

55
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,400
let's make do

56
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:39,367
with this spot.

57
00:06:45,233 --> 00:06:45,800
What?

58
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:18,400
Thank you.

59
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:52,333
If there's anything you're not happy with

60
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:53,000
just let me know.

61
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:03,367
[Episode 8]
[The Sun in the Rain]

62
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:11,433
[3098 Days]

63
00:09:12,967 --> 00:09:18,233
[Day 36 of official cohabitation]

64
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:24,867
Who is it?

65
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:26,400
Who is it?

66
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:27,700
Shuangjiang.

67
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:28,267
Shuangjiang.

68
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,533
Come on, get up.

69
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:30,400
Come on. Let's go.

70
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,067
Get up now.

71
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:31,667
Sorry about this.

72
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:32,233
What are you doing?

73
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:32,867
Listen

74
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:34,600
your mom sold you to us.

75
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:39,600
Stop right there.

76
00:11:05,867 --> 00:11:06,567
Can't sleep?

77
00:11:13,867 --> 00:11:15,267
I just finished showering and here you are.

78
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,767
Your intention is a bit too obvious, you know?

79
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:22,267
You want to see a handsome guy step out of the shower?

80
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,067
Wen Yifan

81
00:12:15,567 --> 00:12:17,400
what's the meaning of this?

82
00:13:33,667 --> 00:13:34,667
How much longer will you hold me?

83
00:13:39,933 --> 00:13:40,600
Wen Yifan?

84
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:14,833
Wen Yifan.

85
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:16,633
You...

86
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:35,767
What was that about?

87
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,333
[Sang Yan: What's going on with you?]

88
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,367
Is he upset?

89
00:15:40,667 --> 00:15:42,867
[What?]

90
00:15:45,433 --> 00:15:47,467
[What?]

91
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:06,300
[Did you text the wrong person?]

92
00:16:26,667 --> 00:16:27,867
What's with the thumbs-up?

93
00:16:31,567 --> 00:16:32,833
Morning encouragement?

94
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:53,567
You messaged me on WeChat yesterday.

95
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:55,000
Anything you wanted to talk about?

96
00:17:09,867 --> 00:17:10,600
What do you mean?

97
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:13,200
You want to pretend it never happened?

98
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,067
Is it because I didn't stay

99
00:17:17,067 --> 00:17:19,000
to finish setting off fireworks with you?

100
00:17:19,367 --> 00:17:20,167
Sorry

101
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,233
if I ruined your mood.

102
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,233
I was just really tired yesterday.

103
00:17:28,533 --> 00:17:29,100
All right.

104
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:35,000
It isn't a big deal

105
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,067
for me

106
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:38,567
but I hope you'll give me

107
00:17:38,567 --> 00:17:39,833
a proper explanation if you do

108
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:41,867
something like this again in the future.

109
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,533
He's so petty.

110
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:53,767
I will.

111
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:07,267
What's that supposed to mean?

112
00:18:12,767 --> 00:18:13,600
Is she not taking responsibility?

113
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:22,667
Morning.

114
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:23,867
Morning.

115
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:29,367
What's wrong?

116
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:30,833
Did you not sleep well?

117
00:18:31,167 --> 00:18:32,600
I've been having restless sleep and frequent dreams.

118
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:33,600
I wonder if this happens

119
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:34,800
to all pregnant women.

120
00:18:35,067 --> 00:18:35,900
That must be tough.

121
00:18:36,467 --> 00:18:37,267
You're going through a lot.

122
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:38,900
How did you sleep last night?

123
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:40,667
I slept okay

124
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,200
but I dreamed all night.

125
00:18:43,267 --> 00:18:43,900
What did you dream about?

126
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:44,967
Tell me.

127
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:46,933
Let me, a modern-day dream expert

128
00:18:46,933 --> 00:18:47,700
interpret it for you.

129
00:18:49,433 --> 00:18:51,033
It'll help me feel more awake.

130
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:57,833
I dreamed

131
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:01,967
that I

132
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:04,233
suddenly wandered into a vast forest.

133
00:19:05,633 --> 00:19:07,267
I walked and walked

134
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,667
searching for an exit

135
00:19:09,033 --> 00:19:10,467
but I just couldn't.

136
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,200
After some time

137
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,433
as I kept moving forward

138
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:21,567
night fell without warning

139
00:19:22,733 --> 00:19:24,533
and the cold crept in.

140
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,733
So I hurried forward.

141
00:19:29,033 --> 00:19:30,367
As I continued walking

142
00:19:30,567 --> 00:19:31,767
I suddenly remembered

143
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,800
that I had seen the sun

144
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:35,367
on my way in.

145
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:00,367
So I thought

146
00:20:01,467 --> 00:20:03,400
maybe I should go back and find it to warm up.

147
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:05,800
After walking for a while

148
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:07,967
I really did find the sun.

149
00:20:10,900 --> 00:20:12,267
Didn't night already fall?

150
00:20:12,667 --> 00:20:13,533
How could there still be a sun?

151
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:16,900
That's why it's a dream.

152
00:20:19,067 --> 00:20:20,067
That's all?

153
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:21,667
So in the end…

154
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:22,633
I found my way out

155
00:20:22,633 --> 00:20:23,767
when I saw the sun.

156
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:39,900
I remember

157
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:43,233
that when I saw it

158
00:20:44,767 --> 00:20:46,067
I couldn't help

159
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,433
but hug it.

160
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,400
This dream...

161
00:21:05,667 --> 00:21:06,533
Is it hard to interpret?

162
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:08,433
Not easy.

163
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,567
[When You Are Old]

164
00:21:22,167 --> 00:21:24,233
[When You Are Old]

165
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:34,100
[I'll lend this to you. Don't just read textbooks.]

166
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:35,833
[Reading poetry helps you dream.]

167
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:43,500
[When you're old, I'll still cherish]

168
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:46,100
[the time we spent together.]

169
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:48,567
By the way

170
00:21:48,567 --> 00:21:50,567
did you get the book I returned to you?

171
00:22:04,533 --> 00:22:08,100
[When you're old, I'll still cherish]

172
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:11,300
[the time we spent together.]

173
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:15,633
[When you're old, I'll still cherish]

174
00:22:15,633 --> 00:22:18,033
[the time we spent together.]

175
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:19,967
There's an urgent task from the higher-ups.

176
00:22:20,067 --> 00:22:22,333
It's about the person from the Central South Century City case last time.

177
00:22:22,433 --> 00:22:24,233
That individual is getting a lot of attention on our channel

178
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:25,867
so the higher-ups want to strike

179
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:27,000
while the iron is hot and do a follow-up.

180
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,767
That person and Yifan went to the same high school

181
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:29,367
so…

182
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:30,000
So

183
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,533
So, have Yifan help you get in touch.

184
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:32,367
The first draft is due tomorrow.

185
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:35,567
She's already handled everything alone during the Spring Festival.

186
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:37,000
We can't have her working overtime again.

187
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,067
All right, Miss?

188
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,533
Here's another task that isn't so urgent.

189
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:43,200
You can take care of it.

190
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:44,567
Okay.

191
00:22:46,733 --> 00:22:47,433
Give it to me.

192
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:49,400
What?

193
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:50,800
Your high school friend's number

194
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:51,867
so you won't feel awkward.

195
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:54,533
Let me ask him for you first.

196
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:55,033
Sure.

197
00:23:06,067 --> 00:23:07,200
Hello and welcome.

198
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:08,067
I'm here to see someone.

199
00:23:08,067 --> 00:23:08,800
This way, please.

200
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:09,367
Okay.

201
00:23:13,833 --> 00:23:14,333
Qiao.

202
00:23:14,467 --> 00:23:15,100
Xiang Lang.

203
00:23:17,667 --> 00:23:19,800
Why did you pick such a fancy restaurant?

204
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:22,067
I thought you wanted a quiet place?

205
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:24,233
You must be hungry.

206
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:25,567
Take a look.

207
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:26,333
- Okay. - See what you'd like to eat.

208
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:29,800
Any recommendations?

209
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,900
We just added a new set menu for couples.

210
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:34,900
We are not...

211
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:37,167
We'll go with the set menu for couples.

212
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:39,000
All right, please wait a moment.

213
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:44,467
Xiang Lang.

214
00:23:45,533 --> 00:23:48,000
Do you remember this bracelet?

215
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:50,600
Isn't this the one I gave you?

216
00:23:50,967 --> 00:23:52,000
You've been wearing it all this time?

217
00:23:53,233 --> 00:23:54,600
I've been wearing it ever since the day

218
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,767
you gave it to me.

219
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:58,000
Even when it didn't match

220
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,600
my outfits

221
00:23:59,633 --> 00:24:00,533
I still kept it on.

222
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:06,767
Qiao, actually…

223
00:24:06,767 --> 00:24:08,200
I've always wanted to ask you this.

224
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,367
When you gave me this bracelet

225
00:24:12,233 --> 00:24:14,000
was it just a birthday gift?

226
00:24:15,167 --> 00:24:17,000
I don't quite understand

227
00:24:17,767 --> 00:24:18,667
what you mean.

228
00:24:18,867 --> 00:24:20,200
I just want to know

229
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,733
if you had even the slightest feelings for me

230
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:25,633
when you gave me

231
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:28,467
this bracelet.

232
00:24:30,367 --> 00:24:30,900
Qiao

233
00:24:31,467 --> 00:24:32,733
did I somehow give you the wrong idea?

234
00:24:34,033 --> 00:24:34,733
I'm sorry.

235
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:36,833
We've always just been close friends.

236
00:24:42,467 --> 00:24:43,333
Seems like

237
00:24:44,333 --> 00:24:45,833
I was reading too much into it.

238
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:53,200
But

239
00:24:56,067 --> 00:24:57,500
is there a chance

240
00:24:58,067 --> 00:24:59,433
you might see me

241
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:02,267
as someone

242
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:06,333
you could be with

243
00:25:06,433 --> 00:25:07,467
from now on?

244
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,000
Actually, I…

245
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,967
I guess the couple's set menu is off the table.

246
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,467
Let's order something else.

247
00:25:19,733 --> 00:25:20,533
Excuse me.

248
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:22,600
I'm here.

249
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:24,633
Have you been waiting for long?

250
00:25:27,433 --> 00:25:28,333
You haven't ordered yet?

251
00:25:30,033 --> 00:25:31,400
I was about to say this earlier.

252
00:25:31,967 --> 00:25:33,233
It's not just the two of us today

253
00:25:35,433 --> 00:25:36,333
but three.

254
00:25:38,567 --> 00:25:40,267
What's happening? It feels a little awkward.

255
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:42,033
No

256
00:25:42,667 --> 00:25:44,400
I misunderstood Xiang Lang.

257
00:25:45,033 --> 00:25:45,867
My bad.

258
00:25:46,533 --> 00:25:48,867
You actually got Qiao to apologize to you?

259
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:50,167
I'm impressed.

260
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,400
Let's order first.

261
00:25:53,533 --> 00:25:54,467
You two eat.

262
00:25:54,467 --> 00:25:55,367
I have to take care of something.

263
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:55,867
Qiao.

264
00:25:57,333 --> 00:25:58,533
What exactly is happening here?

265
00:25:59,967 --> 00:26:00,833
It's all my fault.

266
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,200
Let me explain to both of you.

267
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:08,967
That bracelet

268
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:12,100
was actually something I wanted you

269
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:13,833
to pass on to Dian back then.

270
00:26:16,633 --> 00:26:17,233
Qiao.

271
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:18,900
Xiang Lang.

272
00:26:19,733 --> 00:26:20,533
Sorry

273
00:26:20,533 --> 00:26:21,833
for the last-minute meetup.

274
00:26:22,233 --> 00:26:22,967
No worries.

275
00:26:23,267 --> 00:26:25,000
It's not often that you ask me to meet up.

276
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:30,600
I couldn't change my parents' minds.

277
00:26:31,233 --> 00:26:32,233
They've already booked me

278
00:26:32,233 --> 00:26:33,533
a flight to the U.S. for tomorrow

279
00:26:34,633 --> 00:26:35,400
so

280
00:26:36,267 --> 00:26:37,133
I want to…

281
00:26:38,533 --> 00:26:39,667
I thought you and Dian

282
00:26:39,667 --> 00:26:41,667
had forgotten my birthday.

283
00:26:41,733 --> 00:26:42,533
Thank you.

284
00:26:45,233 --> 00:26:45,800
That's right.

285
00:26:46,167 --> 00:26:46,900
It's your birthday today.

286
00:26:47,467 --> 00:26:48,067
Happy birthday!

287
00:26:48,067 --> 00:26:48,800
Thank you.

288
00:26:49,167 --> 00:26:50,800
This bracelet is gorgeous.

289
00:26:51,033 --> 00:26:52,033
It must have cost a lot, didn't it?

290
00:26:52,967 --> 00:26:53,667
Not really.

291
00:26:54,633 --> 00:26:55,167
So

292
00:26:55,167 --> 00:26:57,367
you said your parents booked you a flight.

293
00:26:57,533 --> 00:26:58,367
What's it for?

294
00:26:58,367 --> 00:26:59,033
A vacation?

295
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:01,667
I'm leaving for the U.S.

296
00:27:02,367 --> 00:27:03,067
to study.

297
00:27:07,333 --> 00:27:08,367
I should have been upfront

298
00:27:09,033 --> 00:27:10,267
with you.

299
00:27:11,067 --> 00:27:11,900
I also

300
00:27:12,767 --> 00:27:14,267
should have confessed my feelings earlier.

301
00:27:15,733 --> 00:27:16,733
This is all on me.

302
00:27:20,433 --> 00:27:21,067
Dian

303
00:27:24,167 --> 00:27:25,667
I've actually

304
00:27:26,567 --> 00:27:28,067
felt differently about you

305
00:27:28,967 --> 00:27:30,067
since high school.

306
00:27:31,067 --> 00:27:32,033
What are you talking about?

307
00:27:39,967 --> 00:27:40,900
It's me who should apologize.

308
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:43,067
I've been deluded

309
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:44,600
holding onto something

310
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:45,833
that wasn't mine for all these years.

311
00:27:47,567 --> 00:27:48,367
You two eat.

312
00:27:48,367 --> 00:27:49,233
I still have work to do.

313
00:27:49,433 --> 00:27:50,367
Qiao.

314
00:27:57,267 --> 00:27:58,000
Dian, I...

315
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:18,667
Ms. Qian...

316
00:28:25,067 --> 00:28:25,633
All right.

317
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:26,833
I'm heading over now.

318
00:28:27,333 --> 00:28:27,867
Dian

319
00:28:28,167 --> 00:28:28,833
where are you going?

320
00:28:29,167 --> 00:28:29,967
I'm going to the TV station.

321
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:32,967
Get in the car. I'll give you a ride.

322
00:28:33,467 --> 00:28:34,267
We can have a chat on the way.

323
00:29:00,367 --> 00:29:01,367
No need to keep wondering.

324
00:29:02,233 --> 00:29:03,433
She's just not into you.

325
00:29:09,867 --> 00:29:10,633
Tell me.

326
00:29:11,167 --> 00:29:12,867
What kind of flirtatious moves did she make?

327
00:29:14,467 --> 00:29:15,567
She hugged you?

328
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:27,833
Since you're both girls

329
00:29:28,167 --> 00:29:29,267
I'd like you to answer this for me.

330
00:29:34,067 --> 00:29:35,633
This person hugged my friend

331
00:29:37,633 --> 00:29:39,367
and acted like nothing happened the next day.

332
00:29:40,633 --> 00:29:41,367
What do you think that means?

333
00:29:44,233 --> 00:29:45,567
Shouldn't this kind of irresponsible behavior

334
00:29:45,567 --> 00:29:46,833
be reported to the police?

335
00:29:53,833 --> 00:29:54,800
It shouldn't be so serious

336
00:29:55,367 --> 00:29:56,400
if it was just a hug, right?

337
00:30:02,567 --> 00:30:03,633
Are you out of your mind?

338
00:30:04,033 --> 00:30:05,333
Why report it to the police?

339
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,200
But really

340
00:30:13,633 --> 00:30:15,767
it depends on the nature of your friend's relationship

341
00:30:15,767 --> 00:30:16,900
with this girl.

342
00:30:18,233 --> 00:30:19,067
Maybe the girl

343
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:21,067
was feeling down

344
00:30:21,067 --> 00:30:22,100
and just needed some comfort

345
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:23,867
so

346
00:30:24,100 --> 00:30:26,033
the hug might not mean much.

347
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:28,067
It could simply be a hug between friends.

348
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:35,000
I'm just speculating, though.

349
00:30:35,433 --> 00:30:35,967
I don't know

350
00:30:35,967 --> 00:30:37,367
their relationship

351
00:30:38,367 --> 00:30:39,400
so my opinion

352
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:41,233
might not be very helpful.

353
00:30:42,467 --> 00:30:43,267
Here's the question.

354
00:30:43,733 --> 00:30:44,800
How's your relationship?

355
00:30:45,267 --> 00:30:47,033
How else could the relationship be?

356
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:48,000
She's my goddess.

357
00:30:48,067 --> 00:30:49,433
I've been pursuing her for over half a year.

358
00:30:49,433 --> 00:30:50,967
And what are you even talking about?

359
00:30:50,967 --> 00:30:52,733
Didn't I explain everything already?

360
00:30:52,767 --> 00:30:53,800
She gave me

361
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:55,333
a box of chocolates on Valentine's Day

362
00:30:55,333 --> 00:30:56,567
not a hug.

363
00:30:57,067 --> 00:30:58,033
The real issue is

364
00:30:58,333 --> 00:30:59,767
that after giving me the chocolates

365
00:30:59,767 --> 00:31:01,267
she never contacted me again.

366
00:31:01,533 --> 00:31:03,967
She's someone who is madly in love with him.

367
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:12,433
Your friend must have quite the charisma.

368
00:31:16,667 --> 00:31:19,067
Did this girl confess to him?

369
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:21,600
Why do you ask?

370
00:31:22,967 --> 00:31:24,900
It just doesn't make sense logically.

371
00:31:26,233 --> 00:31:27,333
If this girl

372
00:31:27,333 --> 00:31:28,333
really likes your friend

373
00:31:28,533 --> 00:31:29,733
then the meaning of the hug

374
00:31:29,733 --> 00:31:30,867
should be pretty clear.

375
00:31:35,367 --> 00:31:36,667
But your friend probably doesn't need

376
00:31:36,667 --> 00:31:38,067
to bring this up with you.

377
00:31:38,267 --> 00:31:39,800
So, are you implying

378
00:31:40,633 --> 00:31:41,733
that love has clouded his judgment?

379
00:31:41,733 --> 00:31:44,067
From what I just heard you say to your friend

380
00:31:44,567 --> 00:31:45,600
it seems like this girl

381
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:46,533
hasn't clearly expressed

382
00:31:46,533 --> 00:31:47,667
her feelings.

383
00:31:51,233 --> 00:31:52,333
So, is it possible

384
00:31:52,333 --> 00:31:53,333
that your friend misunderstood?

385
00:31:53,333 --> 00:31:54,233
Misunderstood?

386
00:31:54,733 --> 00:31:55,400
What did he misunderstand?

387
00:31:57,400 --> 00:31:58,467
Simply put

388
00:31:59,233 --> 00:32:00,167
it's just him

389
00:32:01,600 --> 00:32:02,633
imagining things.

390
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:13,867
Did you hear that?

391
00:32:14,367 --> 00:32:15,667
It's just you imagining things.

392
00:32:16,100 --> 00:32:16,733
Now, leave me alone.

393
00:32:16,733 --> 00:32:17,633
Wait, Sang Yan, what's wrong with...?

394
00:32:33,100 --> 00:32:34,167
Are you done yet?

395
00:32:34,567 --> 00:32:35,633
What's your problem?

396
00:32:38,633 --> 00:32:39,267
It's you.

397
00:32:40,367 --> 00:32:41,467
I thought it was Chen Junwen.

398
00:32:42,233 --> 00:32:43,000
What's the matter?

399
00:32:43,167 --> 00:32:44,700
Su Haoan mentioned in the group chat

400
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:46,333
that you went to Yihe recently.

401
00:32:46,867 --> 00:32:47,367
Were you there for me?

402
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:48,367
What group chat?

403
00:32:48,367 --> 00:32:49,333
How come I didn't see it?

404
00:32:49,467 --> 00:32:50,433
You're not in this group chat.

405
00:32:50,633 --> 00:32:51,800
Seriously?

406
00:32:52,167 --> 00:32:53,100
Is this necessary?

407
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:54,667
Stop changing the subject.

408
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,100
Be honest with me.

409
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:58,433
Have you been to Yihe more than once?

410
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,267
What were you doing there?

411
00:33:40,433 --> 00:33:42,267
You've never loved me, have you?

412
00:33:43,233 --> 00:33:45,000
You've been toying with me, haven't you?

413
00:33:46,467 --> 00:33:47,900
Say something!

414
00:33:49,067 --> 00:33:50,000
Why?

415
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:51,467
Why do you always dress like...?

416
00:34:08,467 --> 00:34:09,100
Sir

417
00:34:09,100 --> 00:34:10,067
I've already bought everything you need

418
00:34:10,067 --> 00:34:11,300
for your stay in the hospital.

419
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:12,400
If there's anything else you need

420
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:13,300
just let me know.

421
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:14,300
Thank you.

422
00:34:14,300 --> 00:34:15,700
The nurse will take you upstairs.

423
00:34:16,867 --> 00:34:17,467
Take care.

424
00:34:19,067 --> 00:34:20,167
Let's go, sir.

425
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:21,233
Bye.

426
00:34:53,200 --> 00:34:55,067
I really don't blame you for this.

427
00:34:55,167 --> 00:34:57,400
I can't blame anyone for things like this.

428
00:34:58,033 --> 00:34:59,967
I probably just need some time.

429
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,833
I don't think you truly understand me.

430
00:35:05,467 --> 00:35:06,467
I tend to avoid things

431
00:35:07,300 --> 00:35:08,300
and I'm not very outgoing.

432
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:10,233
To protect myself

433
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:15,033
I could leave everything behind without hesitation.

434
00:35:16,967 --> 00:35:18,000
The person you imagine me to be

435
00:35:19,633 --> 00:35:21,200
is probably not the same

436
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:22,267
as the one I'm describing.

437
00:35:26,633 --> 00:35:27,867
You really deserve someone better.

438
00:35:35,567 --> 00:35:37,300
I've made things clear with Xiang Lang.

439
00:35:37,833 --> 00:35:39,567
I don't want any misunderstandings between the three of us.

440
00:35:39,767 --> 00:35:41,300
Is it because of me

441
00:35:41,300 --> 00:35:42,067
that you...?

442
00:35:42,067 --> 00:35:43,633
If I really got together with Xiang Lang

443
00:35:43,633 --> 00:35:44,800
would you cut ties with me?

444
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:45,800
Of course not.

445
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:47,100
It's a different time now.

446
00:35:47,233 --> 00:35:49,300
Who would ditch their best friend for a man?

447
00:35:54,933 --> 00:35:57,400
Actually, the main reason I rejected Xiang Lang

448
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,267
is that I don't have

449
00:35:58,267 --> 00:35:59,533
any romantic feelings for him.

450
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:02,867
Just like

451
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:04,533
how he feels about me.

452
00:36:05,167 --> 00:36:06,200
But Xiang Lang

453
00:36:07,167 --> 00:36:08,000
is still

454
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:09,433
a very good friend to us, isn't he?

455
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:21,467
I don't want to grow up at all.

456
00:36:21,933 --> 00:36:22,700
Growing up

457
00:36:22,700 --> 00:36:24,167
just makes everything so complicated.

458
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:26,000
Wouldn't it be better to be as simple as before?

459
00:36:29,767 --> 00:36:31,533
It's love that makes things complicated.

460
00:36:34,533 --> 00:36:35,667
It's inherently an emotion

461
00:36:35,667 --> 00:36:38,467
of extreme love and hate.

462
00:36:46,267 --> 00:36:47,267
Let's sweep away

463
00:36:47,533 --> 00:36:49,533
all the negativity.

464
00:36:52,033 --> 00:36:53,400
Knock them all down with one throw.

465
00:36:53,633 --> 00:36:54,200
Come on.

466
00:36:54,933 --> 00:36:58,067
♪Your eyes can speak♪

467
00:36:58,267 --> 00:37:00,267
♪Even if you try to hide it♪

468
00:37:00,867 --> 00:37:02,167
You just can't let go, can you?

469
00:37:02,167 --> 00:37:02,967
Watch me instead.

470
00:37:03,867 --> 00:37:05,900
♪Yet you're by my side on this journey♪

471
00:37:08,467 --> 00:37:10,100
The one in front of you right now

472
00:37:10,100 --> 00:37:11,633
is from our Lily of the Valley collection.

473
00:37:11,833 --> 00:37:13,467
"Happiness Returns as the Lily of the Valley Blooms

474
00:37:13,467 --> 00:37:14,167
which also symbolizes

475
00:37:14,167 --> 00:37:16,267
a life filled with happiness and fulfillment.

476
00:37:16,967 --> 00:37:17,833
This one looks great.

477
00:37:19,033 --> 00:37:20,400
The other one was too expensive

478
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,033
and it was inconvenient to wear while working.

479
00:37:22,100 --> 00:37:23,100
This one suits me better.

480
00:37:23,933 --> 00:37:25,100
It looks great indeed.

481
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:26,633
It's a brilliant choice.

482
00:37:28,167 --> 00:37:29,667
We should both be kinder to ourselves.

483
00:37:31,533 --> 00:37:33,533
So, are we officially best friends now?

484
00:37:33,667 --> 00:37:35,400
No more annoying guys getting in the way.

485
00:37:36,100 --> 00:37:36,633
Sure.

486
00:37:37,167 --> 00:37:38,867
From now on, there will be no men

487
00:37:38,867 --> 00:37:39,633
only best friends.

488
00:37:45,833 --> 00:37:48,167
♪In this vast world♪

489
00:37:48,467 --> 00:37:50,767
♪I only want to give you my best wishes♪

490
00:37:59,167 --> 00:37:59,833
Thanks.

491
00:38:03,300 --> 00:38:05,300
Here.

492
00:38:05,300 --> 00:38:07,100
It's a good day to get a bit tipsy.

493
00:38:08,033 --> 00:38:09,200
This new lychee flavor

494
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:12,533
is perfect for reminiscing about summer romances.

495
00:38:12,833 --> 00:38:13,467
Try it.

496
00:38:22,167 --> 00:38:23,933
There's something I've been curious about for a while

497
00:38:24,100 --> 00:38:25,100
but I never asked you.

498
00:38:26,567 --> 00:38:27,633
Have you never had

499
00:38:27,633 --> 00:38:29,000
any feelings for Sang Yan before?

500
00:38:32,833 --> 00:38:33,867
Why are you suddenly asking this?

501
00:38:34,033 --> 00:38:35,000
Because he's handsome

502
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:37,300
and he's really quite charming.

503
00:38:37,967 --> 00:38:40,233
Even though I barely talked to him in high school

504
00:38:40,467 --> 00:38:41,300
I knew

505
00:38:41,533 --> 00:38:42,800
that he seemed to really like you

506
00:38:43,267 --> 00:38:44,567
and treated you well.

507
00:38:49,833 --> 00:38:50,767
If you don't say anything

508
00:38:50,767 --> 00:38:52,167
I'll just assume you did have feelings for him.

509
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:55,800
Okay.

510
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,000
So, I can take this as you admit it?

511
00:39:02,600 --> 00:39:03,733
For real?

512
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:06,433
What's with this reaction?

513
00:39:06,767 --> 00:39:08,400
So, you really had feelings for Sang Yan back then?

514
00:39:09,933 --> 00:39:11,467
What about now? Do you still feel the same?

515
00:39:11,867 --> 00:39:13,300
That was long in the past.

516
00:39:13,467 --> 00:39:15,000
But you are roommates now

517
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:16,300
spending so much time around each other.

518
00:39:16,300 --> 00:39:19,200
Besides, you both had feelings for each other before.

519
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:20,633
What if those feelings resurface?

520
00:39:23,367 --> 00:39:24,000
That won't happen.

521
00:39:24,167 --> 00:39:25,433
He's moving out soon.

522
00:39:28,867 --> 00:39:30,100
So you're implying

523
00:39:30,533 --> 00:39:32,000
that if he stayed longer

524
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:33,800
you might have given in to your feelings.

525
00:39:39,033 --> 00:39:41,233
But why didn't you two get together before?

526
00:39:43,200 --> 00:39:44,067
Oh, I get it now.

527
00:39:44,067 --> 00:39:45,700
It was because you transferred schools and moved away

528
00:39:45,700 --> 00:39:47,233
so you lost contact.

529
00:39:51,367 --> 00:39:52,100
No.

530
00:39:52,867 --> 00:39:54,067
Why then?

531
00:40:00,833 --> 00:40:02,567
I don't know if others

532
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,133
would behave the way I do.

533
00:40:04,567 --> 00:40:05,300
But...

534
00:40:08,167 --> 00:40:09,667
But my college roommate once told me

535
00:40:10,267 --> 00:40:11,533
that she thought

536
00:40:12,067 --> 00:40:13,267
I was emotionally distant.

537
00:40:14,033 --> 00:40:15,367
We were close

538
00:40:16,067 --> 00:40:18,167
but once we graduated, it felt like we lost touch.

539
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:21,067
I hardly ever reached out to them

540
00:40:22,700 --> 00:40:24,833
and they were pretty upset about it.

541
00:40:29,667 --> 00:40:31,033
I admit that.

542
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:32,400
Take Xiang Lang, for example.

543
00:40:32,767 --> 00:40:33,667
After he went abroad

544
00:40:33,667 --> 00:40:34,633
we barely kept in touch.

545
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:37,600
I think

546
00:40:38,533 --> 00:40:40,667
it's a natural thing

547
00:40:41,567 --> 00:40:42,567
for people to drift apart

548
00:40:45,033 --> 00:40:46,433
over time.

549
00:40:50,800 --> 00:40:51,800
And back then

550
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:53,567
I just thought

551
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:56,000
someone like Sang Yan

552
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,967
deserved

553
00:41:03,867 --> 00:41:05,633
to be loved passionately.

554
00:41:14,767 --> 00:41:22,167
[Episode 8]
[The Sun in the Rain, Dazzling and Warm]

555
00:41:37,567 --> 00:41:46,033
[The story is not over yet...]

556
00:41:53,567 --> 00:41:54,633
Why does she look

557
00:41:55,267 --> 00:41:56,200
so unhappy?

558
00:42:06,900 --> 00:42:13,633
[To Wen Yifan. Sang Yan: What's going on with you?]

559
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:44,433
Can't sleep?

560
00:42:46,833 --> 00:42:48,267
You want to see a handsome guy step out of the shower?

561
00:43:07,733 --> 00:43:09,067
♪Even the strongest heart♪

562
00:43:09,233 --> 00:43:10,900
♪Can waver♪

563
00:43:11,133 --> 00:43:14,333
♪And doubt its fire♪

564
00:43:14,567 --> 00:43:16,233
♪But you never lost faith in me♪

565
00:43:16,233 --> 00:43:17,900
♪In every battle, every dream I chased♪

566
00:43:18,100 --> 00:43:20,767
♪There is meaning in every step I made♪

567
00:43:21,633 --> 00:43:27,567
♪Through the storm, through the endless night♪

568
00:43:27,933 --> 00:43:29,567
♪You were there, shining like a light♪

569
00:43:29,567 --> 00:43:31,267
♪Warm and bright♪

570
00:43:31,433 --> 00:43:35,133
♪Standing right by my side♪

571
00:43:35,567 --> 00:43:41,700
♪It was you, striding toward me through the storm♪

572
